      "id": "RQ-0059",
      "status": "doing",
      "title": "Return exact native-tool next actions for common browser states",
      "priority": "high",
      "tags": [
        "agent-browser",
        "next-actions",
        "ux",
        "tool-contract"
      ],
      "scope": [
        "extensions/agent-browser/lib/results",
        "extensions/agent-browser/lib/playbook.ts",
        "docs/TOOL_CONTRACT.md",
        "test"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "Agents follow exact tool-call shapes more reliably than prose guidance.",
        "Stable categories should let the wrapper recommend exact calls after open, click, stale refs, downloads, confirmations, and tab drift without guessing from text."
      ],
      "plan": [
        "Define a structured nextActions shape that can express exact `agent_browser` args, optional stdin, sessionMode, reason, and safety notes.",
        "Emit recommendations after common states: open suggests `snapshot -i`; mutating actions suggest wait/snapshot; stale refs suggest fresh snapshot or find locator; downloads point to artifact paths; confirmations suggest confirm/deny; tab drift suggests tab list/tab/snapshot recovery.",
        "Keep recommendations concise and machine-readable while preserving readable summaries for humans.",
        "Add tests that assert exact recommendation payloads and update prompt/playbook docs so agents use them first."
      ],
      "notes": [],
      "request": "Infer and queue exact next-action recommendation work from the user's ABN task list.",
      "created_at": "2026-05-13T13:33:42.731677000Z",
