      "id": "RQ-0061",
      "status": "todo",
      "title": "Add a thin semantic action schema that compiles to existing locator commands",
      "priority": "high",
      "tags": [
        "agent-browser",
        "semantic-actions",
        "find",
        "thin-wrapper"
      ],
      "scope": [
        "extensions/agent-browser",
        "docs/COMMAND_REFERENCE.md",
        "docs/TOOL_CONTRACT.md",
        "test"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "Agents are good at describing intent such as clicking a button named Export or filling a field labeled Email, but brittle CLI token order causes avoidable failures.",
        "The repository already exposes native args/stdin and upstream `find` locators; this task should compile a small intent schema to those primitives rather than build a complex resolver."
      ],
      "plan": [
        "Design a small explicit schema for click/fill/select/check actions using locator families already supported upstream: role, text, label, placeholder, alt, title, and testid.",
        "Compile schema inputs to current `find ... <action>` or equivalent agent-browser commands, returning the exact compiled command in details for debuggability.",
        "Reject ambiguous or unsupported intent with stable categories and exact nextActions rather than guessing.",
        "Add examples and tests for button-by-name, field-by-label, visible-text click, and unsupported/ambiguous targets."
      ],
      "notes": [],
      "request": "Infer and queue simple target-by-meaning support from the user's ABN task list.",
