    {
      "id": "RQ-0062",
      "status": "todo",
      "title": "Recover from stale refs only when retry safety is provable",
      "priority": "high",
      "tags": [
        "agent-browser",
        "stale-refs",
        "recovery",
        "safety"
      ],
      "scope": [
        "extensions/agent-browser",
        "extensions/agent-browser/lib/playbook.ts",
        "docs/TOOL_CONTRACT.md",
        "test"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "Stale refs are a common agent failure mode after navigation, scroll, and rerender.",
        "Automatic recovery is useful only if the wrapper can prove the original action did not execute; destructive or ambiguous actions should return exact recovery calls instead."
      ],
      "plan": [
        "Detect stale-ref failures through the stable category layer across direct actions and batch steps.",
        "Refresh snapshot and attempt to re-identify the intended target using explicit prior ref context or semantic target information when available.",
        "Auto-retry only for safe/idempotent actions or when upstream failure proves the action did not execute; otherwise return nextActions with snapshot/find recovery instructions.",
        "Add regression tests for safe retry, unsafe no-retry, batch behavior, and benchmark impact on stale-ref recovery rate."
      ],
      "notes": [],
      "request": "Infer and queue conservative stale-ref recovery work from the user's ABN task list.",
