        "docs/TOOL_CONTRACT.md",
        "test"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "Common browser work often needs a short open/click/fill/wait/assert/artifact sequence; a thin job runner can reduce calls without hiding upstream behavior.",
        "The repo already supports batch, find locators, wait, and artifact handling, so job mode should orchestrate those primitives, not become a new browser framework."
      ],
      "plan": [
        "Define a constrained job schema with supported steps only: open, click, fill, wait, assert text, assert URL, wait for download, and screenshot on failure.",
        "Compile each job step to existing native args/stdin/sessionMode behavior and include the compiled steps in structured details for auditability.",
        "Stop predictably on failure, emit stable categories, exact nextActions, compact page-change summaries, and verified artifact metadata.",
