      "id": "RQ-0047",
      "status": "todo",
      "title": "Make skills and inspection commands first-class native tool flows",
      "description": "Ensure the wrapper handles upstream inspection surfaces cleanly: `--help`, `--version`, `<command> --help`, `skills list`, `skills get <name> [--full]`, and `skills path [name]`. These commands should be stateless when appropriate, produce readable model-facing output, spill large skill/reference payloads with stable full-output paths, and avoid corrupting harmless documentation examples with over-broad redaction while still redacting real secrets. Acceptance criteria: tests cover skill list/get/path, root and subcommand help, large full-skill compaction, and redaction behavior; outputs remain useful through the native tool without requiring bash; `npm test` passes.",
